[Term]
id: HP:0009145
name: Abnormal cerebral artery morphology
def: "Any structural anomaly of a cerebral artery. The cerebral arteries comprise three main pairs of arteries and their branches, which supply the cerebrum of the brain. These are the anterior cerebral artery, the middle cerebral artery, and the posterior cerebral artery." [https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0736-9199]
synonym: "Abnormality of cerebral artery" EXACT layperson []
synonym: "Abnormality of the cerebral arteries" EXACT layperson []
